{
  "stem": "5371.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in Auschwitz, I didn't travel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But once I was moved to Birkenau--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--then we traveled between camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I want to mention, being in Auschwitz was a month, was in 1943, February.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The, the head of the block, which is the German who was in the head of the block, Olshevsky, told us to undress completely, and made us run to the showers, which is about a city block.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We, we came into the shower and there was cold water.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they let us stay there for about five or six minutes, and then they chased us back out.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was-- must have been outside, freezing, because when I came back to the block, I had chunks of ice on my body.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in fact, one of the, one of them young men fell right dead there, on the run.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then, when we came back to the block, they made us-- he made us sit on the beds, naked, with the windows open on all sides for about two hours.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then they gave us the clothes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And things like this happened on and off in Auschwitz, which I don't recall any of-- every little incident, but there were many incidents of beating, and for little-- any little thing.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "One day, I remember, while I was working still in Auschwitz, we were putting up on the remaining one-story building, we were putting up a second floor.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The Polacks sent me to the kitchen, to the camp kitchen.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they told me-- they gave me a pail, and clay, and tools, and a rag.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I should go into the camp kitchen, in one of the rooms where the-- they had basins with peeled potatoes for the SS.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
